--- Preliminary Notes and Requirements

* We use the python package Scrapy (https://scrapy.org/)

* We use bash scripts to move Scrapy results

* The directory containing this README is the base directory; call it BASE_DIR.



--- Part 1:  Use scrapy to scrape the speeches

----- Scrape State of the Unions

* Change directory to the scrapy project.

> cd BASE_DIR/presidential_speech/

* Scrape the speeches

> scrapy crawl sou_text

* Go back to BASE_DIR and move the results via move_sou_results.sh

> cd BASE_DIR
> ./move_sou_results.sh

----- Scrape Inaugurals

* Change directory to the scrapy project.

> cd BASE_DIR/presidential_speech/

* Scrape the speeches

> scrapy crawl inaug_text

* Go back to BASE_DIR and move the results via move_inaug_results.sh

> cd BASE_DIR
> ./move_inaug_results.sh


----- Scrape Conventions

* Change directory to the scrapy project.

> cd BASE_DIR/presidential_speech/

* Scrape the speeches

> scrapy crawl conv_text

* Go back to BASE_DIR and move the results via move_conv_results.sh

> cd BASE_DIR
> ./move_conv_results.sh



--- Part 2: Generate Dataset


> cd BASE_DIR/create_dataset
> Rscript create_dataset.R


